The paper deals with natural language processing and machine translation, which are core topics in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed framework involves collaboration between a human scholar and a machine, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and deep learning (cs.DL) techniques. The paper also mentions the need for information retrieval (cs.IR) and language generation (cs.LG) methods.
